{
  "stem": "13395.6",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Can't even tell you what were the thoughts we had.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I only thought of my mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I was glad he sent everybody into the barracks, that she wouldn't witness it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[SOBBING] It was better to die then than later.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It didn't matter.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Then he suddenly said, I'm going to count to 10.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And when I count to 10, I don't see any one of you out here.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "You can run to the barrack.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Anyone who's left outside is shot.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He took out the pistol.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And he makes it ready, whatever you do with a pistol.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he starts counting.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we start running on that ice and on that snow, and trying to get on the stairs into the barrack and pushing in through that narrow door.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "You only think of yourself.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I want to live, not my friend, not the girl behind me or in front of me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I want to be through that door and save my life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "It's something you'd never do-- enormous circumstances.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "What I'm trying to say is, this is the way they dehumanized us, that we didn't care about our fellow prisoners.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "That suddenly, in that moment, you cared about yourself.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "That explains it all.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "That explains how people behaved in a time like this.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "How many people are being accused of working with the Nazis or for the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But if a man had a family at home and thought that this will save his family, in a time like this, you've got to be in his shoes, and you can never be in his shoes unless you were there.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And you can never sit in judgment.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And that moment when I tried to get through that door before any of my fellow prisoners, I understood what they did to us.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
